A \in M_n(\mathbb R)
M_A(t)=\prod_{i=1}^{k}(t-\lambda_i)^{\textstyle s_i}.
\lambda _1,\lambda_2,\lambda _3,......,\lambda _k
B\in M_{2n}(\mathbb R)
\left(\begin{matrix} A &I_n \\  0 & A \end{matrix}\right)
B
M_B(t)=\prod_{i=1}^k(t-\lambda_i)^{\textstyle s_{i}+1}.
B = \pmatrix{A & I \cr 0 & A\cr}
p
p(B) = \pmatrix{ p(A) & p'(A)\cr 0 & p(A)\cr}
p(t)
p'(t)
(t - \lambda)^j
p(t)
(t - \lambda)^{j+1}
P
 P(B) = P\left( \begin{bmatrix} A & I \\ I & A \end{bmatrix} \right) = \frac{1}{2} \begin{bmatrix} P(A+I)+P(A-I) & P(A+I)-P(A-I) \\ P(A+I)-P(A-I) & P(A+I)+P(A-I) \end{bmatrix}. 
P(B)=0 \Leftrightarrow P(A+I) = P(A-I) = 0.
